Thirteen people have been injured when the taxi that they were travelling in careened off the highway and landed head first against a tree on the M13, near Salisbury this morning, (Friday, 28 February)    Rescue Care Paramedics arrived on the scene to find carnage. The vehicle was found down the bank. More ambulances as well as rescue technicians were dispatched to the scene to assist. “Fortunately there were no entrapments, however, thirteen people had sustained injuries ranging from minor to serious. Once all of the injured were stabilised at the scene, they were transported to various Durban hospitals for the further care that they required,” said Garrith Jamieson of Rescue Care.  At this stage the events leading up to the crash is unknown however SAPS will be investigating further.